      <scopecontent id="aspace_f89119c3e4e15434c3df02dfd06c7d09">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Vivian Prewett Papers consist of the letters of Vivian J. A. Prewett, a trooper with the 13th Company, Imperial Yeomanry. Prewett corresponded with family and friends during his tour of duty fighting the Boers from January 1900 - January 1901.</p>
         <p>The letters chronicle Prewett's anticipation of sailing to South Africa, his arrival in Cape Town, the daily routine of camp life, his participation in combat as well as Prewett's personal observations of the Boers and of England's involvement in the war.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
